                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2rb">Fol. 2rb</locus>: Excerpt from the Epistle of John (1 Jn. 1:1-17).<q xml:lang="gez">Fol: 2rb: መልእክተ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ሐዋርያት…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Probably written as a writing exercise (s. EAE II, 340).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2vb">Fol. 2vb</locus>: Excerpt from an unidentified text (?).<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 2vb: ቆቁ፡ በከርሠ፡ ገሀነም፡ ወልድኪ፡ ንጽሐ፡ ሥጋኪ…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#4ra">Fol. 4ra</locus>-vb: Hymn to the Virgin Mary.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 4ra-4vb: ኵሉሙ፡ ሠራዊተ፡ መላእክት፡ ይሴብሁኪ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Identical to EMML 1593 (s. EMML V, 78). Incomplete.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#164ra">Fol. 164ra</locus>: Ownership note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 164ra: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘቀዳሜ፡ ቃል፡ {አጽሀፍዎ፡ ድብረ፡ ማርያም፡} ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጕዘ፡ ለይኩን።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note refers to a certain Qädame Qal, previously not mentioned but possibly related to ʾAmdä Mikaʾel (s. the supplication formula on fol. 163rb); the name of the latter was also probably included in the note, but washed out. Instead, a secondary hand added, in black ink, the words: "(the community) of Däbrä Maryam caused it to be written".
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#164rb">Fol. 164rb</locus>: Mälkǝʾ-hymn to Jesus Christ.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 164rb: ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ እስም[sic] ፡ መሐላ፡ ዘኢይሔሱ።...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Cp. ChRep no. 123.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#164rb">Fol. 164rb</locus>: Sälam-hymn to Virgin Mary.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 164rb: ሰላም፡ ለኪ፡ ዕንዘ፡ ንሰገድ፡ ንብለኪ።...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Cp. ChRep no. 95.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus target="#164v">Fol. 164v</locus>: Unidentified hymn (on St. Täklä Haymanot?).<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 164v: ለእግዚእ፡ ኃረያ፡ ሠናይት፡ ወለጸጋ፡ ዘአብ፡ አዳም።...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <locus target="#170v">Fol. 170v</locus>: Acquision note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 170v: ዝገድል፡ ዘተገዝአ፡ በብዙኀ፡ ወርቅ፡ ወብረር፡ ዘሐሬነት፡ ገበዘይት…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 170v: This Vita has been bought with much gold and silver of Ḥarennät Gäbäzäyti...</q>
                           The note states that the Ms. was bought with the means of the church of Ḥarennät Gäbäzäyti.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Excerpt from the Ethiopian syllabary, probably a writing exercise: fol. 2ra. &#xD;
- Writing exercise: fol. 3r.&#xD;
